1
00:00:01,935 --> 00:00:03,802
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.    


2
00:00:03,870 --> 00:00:06,771
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>HIS NAME IS ANGELO.</i>             
<i>THINK OF HIM LIKE A SPONGE--</i>    


3
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:09,708
<i>SOMEONE WHO CAN ABSORB</i>          
<i>THE INTELLECTUAL, EMOTIONAL,</i>    


4
00:00:09,776 --> 00:00:12,277
<i>EVEN THE PHYSICAL</i>               
<i>TRAITS OF OTHERS.</i>               


5
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:14,346
<i>HE WILL FIND JAROD FOR US.</i>      


6
00:00:14,415 --> 00:00:17,216
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>HE BETTER, SYDNEY.</i>              
<i>HE JUST BETTER.</i>                 


7
00:00:20,887 --> 00:00:23,255
<i>[ Keyboard Clacking ]</i>           


8
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:29,494
                YES, MR. PARKER.


9
00:00:29,563 --> 00:00:33,298
    HE'S SEARCHING THE INTERNET 
    FOR ANY SIGNS OF HIM NOW.   


10
00:00:34,401 --> 00:00:36,334
            <i> WE'LL FIND JAROD...</i>


11
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:40,738
            <i> AND WHOEVER</i>        
            <i> INSIDE THE CENTRE</i>  
            <i> IS HELPING HIM.</i>    


12
00:00:40,807 --> 00:00:43,108
            <i> [ Phone Hangs Up ]</i> 


13
00:00:43,177 --> 00:00:47,278
KEEP WORKING, ANGELO.           


14
00:00:47,347 --> 00:00:49,614
        KEEP WORKING.           


15
00:00:54,321 --> 00:00:57,889
    [ Explosion]                
                    <i> [ Man ]</i>    
                    <i> WHOO-WHEE!</i> 


16
00:00:57,958 --> 00:01:00,725
            YOU SEE?            
            GET TOO CLOSE       
            TO THAT BAD BOY...  


17
00:01:00,794 --> 00:01:03,428
    AND YOU'LL BE A-PICKING     
    YOUR NOSE WITH YOUR WRIST.  


18
00:01:03,497 --> 00:01:07,465
            <i> [ Chuckling ]</i>      
            <i> NOW, YOU BOYS</i>      
            <i> ARE 21, AREN'T YA?</i> 


19
00:01:10,203 --> 00:01:12,671
        THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.  


20
00:01:12,740 --> 00:01:14,740
            FILL UP             
            THEIR TRUNK, EUGENE.


21
00:01:17,011 --> 00:01:21,145
    -<i> NOW, WHERE WERE WE?</i>       
    - YOU WERE TELLING US       
      ABOUT MR. NOBEL.          


22
00:01:21,214 --> 00:01:25,450
YEAH, OLD NOBEL WAS LIKE        
A PICASSO OF GUNPOWDER.         


23
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:29,955
    - HE INVENTED               
      THE BIG BERTHA, YOU KNOW. 
    - THE BIG BERTHA?           


24
00:01:30,023 --> 00:01:33,758
THE MOTHER OF ALL ROMAN CANDLES.
THREE TIME-DELAYED              
SPARKLE EXPLOSIONS...           


25
00:01:33,827 --> 00:01:36,594
WRAPPED IN A COLOR-SPRAY        
SMOKE BANGER,                   


26
00:01:36,663 --> 00:01:39,798
LINED WITH QUARTER STRANDS      
OF T.N.T.                       


27
00:01:39,867 --> 00:01:42,967
    - SOUNDS IMPRESSIVE.        
    - PUT ON                    
      A NEW YEAR'S EVE SHOW...  


28
00:01:43,036 --> 00:01:45,003
THAT PUT OLD DICKIE CLARK       
TO SHAME.                       


29
00:01:45,071 --> 00:01:49,974
<i>[ Chuckling ]</i>                   
<i>I DON'T KNOW WHERE HE WENT.</i>     
<i>JUST DISAPPEARED.</i>               


30
00:01:50,043 --> 00:01:51,809
    YES.                        
                        HMM.    


31
00:01:51,878 --> 00:01:55,480
HE HAS A HABIT                  
OF DOING THAT.                  
THANK YOU.                      


32
00:01:55,549 --> 00:01:59,384
THERE IS NO WAY                 
THAT JAROD COULD HAVE           
KNOWN WE WERE COMING.           


33
00:01:59,453 --> 00:02:02,254
        ZERO.                   


34
00:02:02,322 --> 00:02:07,158
HAVE YOU NOTICED THAT           
IT NEVER SEEMS TO WORK          
THE OTHER WAY, SYD?             


35
00:02:07,227 --> 00:02:10,095
MAYBE THERE IS A REASON.        


36
00:02:16,303 --> 00:02:18,303
STAY FROSTY, NOBEL.             


37
00:02:18,372 --> 00:02:21,340
<i>IT'S ALL BEING RECORDED</i>         
<i>FOR POSTERITY.</i>                  


38
00:02:22,976 --> 00:02:25,543
                    THIS WAY.   


39
00:02:27,614 --> 00:02:31,516
THE NOTE THAT WAS FAXED SAID    
WE'D FIND THE BOMB OVER HERE.   


40
00:02:36,957 --> 00:02:39,991
<i>CARLSON.</i>                        
            [ Beeping ]         


41
00:02:40,059 --> 00:02:42,059
                    HELLO.      


42
00:02:45,299 --> 00:02:49,000
OH, YEAH.                       


43
00:02:49,069 --> 00:02:51,502
<i>BAD BETTY.</i>                      


44
00:02:51,571 --> 00:02:54,005
    FAX BOMBER'S USUAL.         


45
00:02:55,275 --> 00:02:57,909
                <i> WHOA, COWBOY.</i>  


46
00:02:57,977 --> 00:03:02,047
BETTY NEEDS HER BEAUTY REST,    
OR SHE'S A REAL WITCH           
TO WAKE UP NEXT TO.             


47
00:03:02,115 --> 00:03:04,416
            TOOLS.              


48
00:03:10,724 --> 00:03:14,359
<i>WHOA. I FOUND SOMETHING.</i>        


49
00:03:14,427 --> 00:03:17,228
            <i> LOOKS LIKE A NOTE.</i> 
    HE ALWAYS LEAVES ONE.       


50
00:03:25,972 --> 00:03:28,606
        WHAT'S IT SAY?          


51
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:32,109
    "CATCH ME IF YOU CAN,       
     YOU MISCREANTS."           


52
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:34,779
    "MISCREANTS"?               
    WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?        


53
00:03:34,848 --> 00:03:38,382
            <i> [ Rapid Beeping ]</i>  


54
00:03:38,451 --> 00:03:42,386
    IT MEANS "GET THE HELL      
    OUTTA HERE"! MOVE! MOVE!    


55
00:03:52,699 --> 00:03:55,400
    [ Coughing ]                


56
00:04:01,140 --> 00:04:03,407
IS IT ALWAYS LIKE THIS?         


57
00:04:05,145 --> 00:04:08,579
WELCOME TO                      
THE BOMB SQUAD, JAROD.          


58
00:04:14,054 --> 00:04:17,622
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


59
00:05:01,534 --> 00:05:04,336
<i>[ Chatter On Police Radio ]</i>     


60
00:05:10,577 --> 00:05:12,777
                SO, NOBEL,      
                NOW YOU KNOW... 


61
00:05:12,846 --> 00:05:16,214
WHAT A CLOSE ENCOUNTER WITH     
THE FAX BOMBER FEELS LIKE, HUH? 


62
00:05:16,283 --> 00:05:18,983
                    MM-HMM.     


63
00:05:19,053 --> 00:05:21,053
MAN, I WISH                     
I COULD HAVE BEEN HERE.         


64
00:05:21,121 --> 00:05:23,088
    CAN'T IMAGINE WHY, SIR.     


65
00:05:23,157 --> 00:05:26,891
- MY EARS ARE STILL RINGING.    
- USED TO BE SOME SCUMBALL      
  WENT TO MAKE A BOMB THREAT,   


66
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,893
THEY'D PICK UP THE PHONE        
LIKE A DECENT HUMAN BEING.      


67
00:05:28,962 --> 00:05:31,228
NOW WHAT?                       
THEY FAX 'EM IN.                


68
00:05:31,297 --> 00:05:34,098
    - SCUMBALL?                 
    - SORT OF LIKE A MISCREANT, 
      ONLY DIFFERENT.           


69
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:37,235
[ Forced Laughing ]             
SOMEONE MARK THE CALENDAR.      
LAMONT MADE A FUNNY.            


70
00:05:37,304 --> 00:05:40,205
        <i> NOW, THIS BOMBER</i>       
        <i> FAXES HIS THREATS IN.</i>  


71
00:05:40,273 --> 00:05:43,608
THAT'S A UNIQUE M.O.            
MUST HELP HIM COVER HIS TRACKS. 


72
00:05:43,677 --> 00:05:46,777
    <i> WELL, THIS GUY DOESN'T NEED</i>
    <i> ANY HELP. WE HAVE RUN...</i>   


73
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:50,715
    EVERY PIECE OF EVIDENCE     
    HE'S LEFT BEHIND THROUGH    
    THE BEST TECHNOLOGY WE HAVE:


74
00:05:50,783 --> 00:05:54,852
        D.N.A., HAIR SAMPLES,   
        FIBER, IMPRESSIONOLOGY--


75
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:56,921
        GUY LEAVES US NOTHING   
        TO FOLLOW. NOTHING.     


76
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:58,956
            <i> WE GOTTA CATCH</i>     
            <i> A BREAK SOMETIME.</i>  


77
00:05:59,025 --> 00:06:02,394
SO YOU, UH-- YOU PEOPLE, YOU    
STAY HERE AND KEEP AFTER THIS.  


78
00:06:02,462 --> 00:06:04,595
            I'M GONNA GO        
            LIE TO THE PRESS.   


79
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,701
    [ Groans ]                  


80
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:11,869
    WHAT'S THE MATTER, CARLSON? 
    YOU CATCH A LITTLE MORE     
    STEEL LAST NIGHT?           


81
00:06:11,938 --> 00:06:16,141
<i>HEY, LAMONT, WHY DON'T YOU BE</i>   
<i>A GOOD CIVIL SERVANT? GET</i>       
<i>THE TWO HEROES SOME COFFEE.</i>     


82
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,043
            HE LOVES ME.        


83
00:06:18,111 --> 00:06:20,445
    DID YOU HAVE ANOTHER BOMB   
    GO OFF ON YOU BEFORE?       


84
00:06:20,513 --> 00:06:22,480
I GOT A LITTLE SHRAPNEL         
IN MY SHOULDER DURING THE WAR.  


85
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:25,149
<i>HERO HERE'S THE ONLY GUY</i>        
<i>REFERS TO GRENADA AS A WAR.</i>     


86
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:28,386
-<i> I GOT THE MEDALS TO PROVE IT.</i> 
-<i> COME ON. YOU KNOW</i>             
<i>  THE ONLY MEDALS...</i>            


87
00:06:28,455 --> 00:06:32,156
THAT COUNT                      
IN YOUR FAMILY ARE THE ONES     
YOUR BIG BROTHER WON IN 'NAM.   


88
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:34,892
I HEARD THAT YOU BROUGHT        
THE LAST TWO OF THE FAX BOMBER'S
DEVICES IN INTACT.              


89
00:06:34,962 --> 00:06:38,697
I GOT LUCKY. HEY.               
DON'T YOU WORRY ABOUT IT, J.    


90
00:06:38,766 --> 00:06:40,832
<i>ONE DAY THIS FAX BOMBER'S</i>       
<i>GONNA SLIP UP.</i>                  


91
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:43,668
WHEN HE DOES, WE'RE GONNA       
BE THERE TO CATCH HIM.          


92
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:46,804
        I JUST HOPE THE S.O.B.  
        BLOWS HIMSELF UP.       


93
00:06:46,873 --> 00:06:50,308
<i>[ Man ] THE DETONATOR WAS</i>       
<i>CONNECTED TO AN ACCELERATOR.</i>    


94
00:06:50,377 --> 00:06:55,280
            THIS IS A DANGEROUS 
            NEW ESCALATION      
            FOR THE FAX BOMBER. 


95
00:06:55,349 --> 00:06:57,315
                HAND THOSE OUT, 
                WILL YOU, JOHN? 


96
00:06:57,384 --> 00:06:59,484
        THIS IS MY SIGHT PROFILE
        OF THE BOMBER.          


97
00:06:59,553 --> 00:07:03,387
            IT INCLUDES A, UH,  
            COMPUTER-GENERATED  
            COMPOSITE SKETCH... 


98
00:07:03,456 --> 00:07:05,489
        BASED ON SOME           
        INCOMPLETE INFORMATION. 


99
00:07:05,558 --> 00:07:09,561
HE LOOKS LIKE MY UNCLE FRED.    
        LOOKS LIKE              
        EVERYONE'S UNCLE FRED.  


100
00:07:09,629 --> 00:07:13,098
            <i> BASED ON HIS, UH,</i>  
            <i> FAXED THREATS</i>      
            <i> AND OTHER DATA,</i>    


101
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:17,002
<i>THE BOMBER IS A LEFT-HANDED,</i>    
<i>DISGRUNTLED EX-CITY WORKER.</i>     


102
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:20,772
    THE CHANCES ARE HE'S ALREADY
    EXPRESSED HIS DISCONTENT.   


103
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:24,575
- WE ALL KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.  
- BACK TO THE CRANK FILES.      


104
00:07:24,644 --> 00:07:27,512
    EXCELLENT, LAMONT.          
    NOW, I EXPECT...            


105
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:30,514
<i>THAT ALL OF YOU PEOPLE</i>          
<i>WILL PUT IN WHATEVER</i>            
<i>OVERTIME IS NECESSARY...</i>        


106
00:07:30,583 --> 00:07:35,720
TO SCREEN THOSE FILES           
AND TO INTERVIEW                
EVERY POSSIBLE PERP.            


107
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:39,958
QUESTIONS? NO? GOOD.            
GO TO WORK.                     


108
00:07:43,796 --> 00:07:46,998
EXCUSE ME. LIEUTENANT CHOMSKY,  
DO YOU HAVE A MOMENT?           
            SURE.               


109
00:07:47,067 --> 00:07:50,935
I'VE BEEN GOING OVER            
YOUR FILE ON THE FAX BOMBER,    
AND WITH ALL DUE RESPECT, SIR-- 


110
00:07:51,004 --> 00:07:56,207
YOU KNOW, WHEN PEOPLE SAY,      
"ALL DUE RESPECT,"              
THEY GENERALLY DON'T HAVE IT.   


111
00:07:56,276 --> 00:08:00,044
SIR, IT-IT'S JUST THAT          
I THINK THAT YOUR PROFILE       
OF THE PERP...                  


112
00:08:00,113 --> 00:08:03,381
IS EXACTLY WHO                  
HE WANTS US TO THINK HE IS.     


113
00:08:03,449 --> 00:08:07,485
I THINK THAT HIS GRUDGE AGAINST 
THE CITY AND EVERYTHING ELSE    
ABOUT HIM IS A MISLEAD.         


114
00:08:07,554 --> 00:08:10,388
            GUY'S HERE A WEEK,  
            HE'S ALREADY        
            BUCKING FOR MY BARS.


115
00:08:10,456 --> 00:08:12,757
NO, SIR. I JUST HAPPEN          
TO HAVE A DIFFERENT OPINION.    


116
00:08:12,826 --> 00:08:16,127
                BASED ON WHAT?  
I KNOW PEOPLE.                  


117
00:08:16,196 --> 00:08:18,563
                I'M LISTENING.  


118
00:08:18,631 --> 00:08:20,565
THE D.N.A.                      
AND THE IMPRESSIONOLOGY...      


119
00:08:20,633 --> 00:08:22,566
ALL CAME UP EMPTY.              


120
00:08:22,636 --> 00:08:25,536
HE'S TRYING TO LEAD US          
DOWN A HIGH-TECH PATH,          


121
00:08:25,605 --> 00:08:29,007
BUT I BELIEVE                   
THAT WE CAN SNAG HIM            
WITH A LOW-TECH SOLUTION.       


122
00:08:29,075 --> 00:08:31,142
HE'S RIGHT-HANDED,              


123
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:33,411
BUT HE WANTS US                 
TO BELIEVE HE'S A LEFTY.        


124
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:36,081
THE VERTICALS                   
AND THE HORIZONTALS             
ARE ALL JAGGED,                 


125
00:08:36,149 --> 00:08:39,984
WHICH WOULD INDICATE            
THAT HE'S BEEN WRITING          
WITH HIS SUBDOMINANT HAND.      


126
00:08:40,053 --> 00:08:44,589
        YOU'RE A GRAPHOLOGIST?  
UH, NO, SIR, BUT I WAS          
A PALM READER ONCE.             


127
00:08:44,658 --> 00:08:47,258
        SHALL I TELL YOU        
        ABOUT YOUR FUTURE HERE? 


128
00:08:47,327 --> 00:08:51,462
SIR, I BELIEVE                  
THAT OUR BOMBER...              


129
00:08:51,531 --> 00:08:55,433
IS A CITY EMPLOYEE WHO IS NOT   
NECESSARILY DISGRUNTLED.        


130
00:08:55,502 --> 00:08:58,169
HE'S ENJOYING                   
WATCHING US RUN AROUND...       


131
00:08:58,238 --> 00:09:02,473
ALMOST AS MUCH AS HE ENJOYS     
SETTING OFF EXPLOSIONS.         


132
00:09:02,542 --> 00:09:06,745
    IF YOU WANT TO SUGGEST THAT,
    UH, THIS CLOWN IS SOME KIND 
    OF A MERRY PRANKSTER,       


133
00:09:06,813 --> 00:09:09,848
        I RECOMMEND THAT YOU    
        TALK WITH RACHEL NEWTON.


134
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,016
    RACHEL IS GONNA SPEND       
    THE NEXT YEAR OF HER LIFE...


135
00:09:12,085 --> 00:09:14,185
    LEARNING HOW TO READ BRAILLE
    BECAUSE OF THE FAX BOMBER.  


136
00:09:14,254 --> 00:09:17,188
I WASN'T TRYING                 
TO TRIVIALIZE THAT, SIR.        
    NO, NO. I KNOW YOU WEREN'T. 


137
00:09:17,257 --> 00:09:20,125
        YOU WERE JUST TRYING TO 
        MAKE, UH, AN IMPRESSION,


138
00:09:20,193 --> 00:09:22,794
        SHOW OFF YOUR ERUDITE   
        EUROPEAN UPBRINGING.    


139
00:09:22,862 --> 00:09:25,864
MY WHAT?                        
                THE CADENCE     
                IN YOUR VOICE-- 


140
00:09:25,932 --> 00:09:30,034
    YOU WERE RAISED BY          
    A FRENCH NANNY. WELL,       
    COULD BE BELGIAN, I SUPPOSE.


141
00:09:30,103 --> 00:09:34,071
HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?          
            OH, I KNOW          
            ABOUT PEOPLE TOO.   


142
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:37,041
            <i> [ Sydney Speaking</i>  
            <i> Foreign Language ]</i> 


143
00:09:37,110 --> 00:09:40,878
            [ Continues ]       


144
00:09:40,947 --> 00:09:44,015
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>DAMN IT, BROOTS.</i>                
<i>YOU SAID WE HAD HIM CORNERED.</i>   


145
00:09:44,084 --> 00:09:46,150
BUT WE DID.                     
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED.     


146
00:09:46,219 --> 00:09:50,989
                JAROD HAPPENED. 
        OH, SPARE ME, SYDNEY.   


147
00:09:51,057 --> 00:09:53,190
        ALL I KNOW IS           
        THAT I'M FED UP...      


148
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:55,727
        WITH ALWAYS BEING       
        A STEP BEHIND HIM.      


149
00:09:55,795 --> 00:09:58,229
                <i> [ Raines ]</i>     
                <i> SO AM I.</i>       


150
00:10:02,669 --> 00:10:07,204
    - UH, I-I GOTTA GO.         
    - STAY HERE, MR. BROOTS.    


151
00:10:07,273 --> 00:10:10,408
    - WHAT BRINGS YOU DOWN      
      FROM THE TOWER, SIR?      
    - PLUMBING.                 


152
00:10:10,477 --> 00:10:13,110
            PLUMBING?           


153
00:10:13,179 --> 00:10:15,547
            I'VE COME           
            TO PLUG A LEAK.     


154
00:10:23,757 --> 00:10:27,024
    -<i> HEY.</i>                      
    - HEY. WHAT'S UP, NOBEL?    


155
00:10:27,093 --> 00:10:30,562
THE FAX BOMBER,                 
A.K.A. UNCLE FRED.              


156
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,797
            OKAY.               
            NOT MY FINEST HOUR, 
            BUT, HEY,           


157
00:10:32,865 --> 00:10:37,268
    NOBODY GOT A GREAT LOOK     
    AT THIS GUY, SO THE SKETCH  
    IS, YOU KNOW, SKETCHY.      


158
00:10:37,337 --> 00:10:39,270
THIS IS                         
A FASCINATING MACHINE.          


159
00:10:39,339 --> 00:10:42,607
        YEAH. THIS HERE IS      
        A DECATRONICS TURBO     
        GRAPHICS II WORKSTATION.


160
00:10:42,676 --> 00:10:46,978
    THIS LITTLE BAD BOY         
    MAKES COMPOSITES,           
    PUTS DISGUISES ON PORTRAITS,


161
00:10:47,046 --> 00:10:52,449
<i>AGES MISSING KIDS,</i>              
<i>WHICH IS WHAT I'M DOING NOW.</i>    


162
00:10:52,518 --> 00:10:56,220
<i>THAT'S INCREDIBLE.</i>              
<i>SOME OF MY BEST WORK'S BEEN</i>     
<i>ON THE BACKS OF MILK CARTONS.</i>   


163
00:10:56,289 --> 00:10:58,556
    <i> [ Chuckling ]</i>              
    <i> THINK OF THE D.T.G. II...</i>  


164
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:00,458
        AS SORT OF A HIGH-TECH  
        MR. POTATO HEAD.        


165
00:11:00,526 --> 00:11:03,627
        - MISTER WHO?           
        - POTATO HEAD.          


166
00:11:03,696 --> 00:11:07,732
<i>OH. NOW,</i>                        
<i>THIS IS INTERESTING.</i>            


167
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:11,435
YOU CALL HIM MR. POTATO HEAD,   
YET HIS HEAD IS                 
HIS WHOLE BODY?                 


168
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:13,304
                    YEAH.       
                    COOL, HUH?  


169
00:11:13,373 --> 00:11:15,406
HE COMES WITH LITTLE            
INTERCHANGEABLE EARS,           


170
00:11:15,474 --> 00:11:17,608
                EYES            
                AND LITTLE HATS.


171
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:21,479
    OLD SPUD MAN IS THE ORIGINAL
    MASTER OF DISGUISE.         


172
00:11:21,548 --> 00:11:24,315
YOU KNOW, THIS WOULD MAKE       
A WONDERFUL TOY FOR CHILDREN.   


173
00:11:26,252 --> 00:11:29,887
    HEY, NOBEL, CRANK FILE      
    JUST TURNED UP A HOT ONE.   
    LET'S RUN.                  


174
00:11:29,956 --> 00:11:32,090
    HMM.                        
<i>[ Doorbell Ringing ]</i>            


175
00:11:34,828 --> 00:11:37,061
                OH, GOD.        
                WHAT'D HE DO?   


176
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:40,798
        CURTIS! THEY FINALLY    
        CAME TO ARREST YOU!     


177
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:45,770
        CURTIS!                 
                    <i> BUSY, MA!</i>  


178
00:11:45,839 --> 00:11:48,940
            MRS. HARING,        
            WE'RE NOT HERE      
            TO ARREST YOUR SON. 


179
00:11:49,009 --> 00:11:52,109
I KNEW SOMEDAY THE COPS WOULD   
SHOW UP AND TAKE HIM AWAY.      


180
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:56,447
    <i> - CURTIS!</i>                  
    <i> - I SAID, GET OFF MY BACK!</i> 


181
00:11:56,515 --> 00:11:59,884
- MA'AM, WE JUST WANTED TO--    
- THIRTY YEARS OLD, AND HE      
  STILL LIVES IN MY BASEMENT.   


182
00:11:59,953 --> 00:12:02,687
DAY IN AND DAY OUT,             
WRITING HIS LITTLE LETTERS.     


183
00:12:02,756 --> 00:12:05,022
    I SHOULD'VE BOUGHT          
    STOCK IN BIC.               


184
00:12:05,091 --> 00:12:08,626
    DON'T SAY NOTHING, MA.      
    THIS IS ALL GOING ON TAPE   
    SOMEWHERE. I KNOW IT.       


185
00:12:08,694 --> 00:12:11,996
LISTEN TO THAT.                 
DO YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S DONE      
TO MY SOCIAL LIFE...            


186
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:13,998
<i>HAVING HIM</i>                      
<i>DOWN THERE?</i>                     


187
00:12:14,067 --> 00:12:17,936
            YOU'RE NOT GETTIN'  
            NOTHIN' OUT OF ME.  
I'M IN THE PRIME OF MY LIFE.    


188
00:12:18,004 --> 00:12:21,839
I SHOULD GO OUT,                
GET MYSELF SOME NICE SHOES      
AND FIND MYSELF A MAN.          


189
00:12:21,908 --> 00:12:25,909
            - MA!               
            - SIR,              


190
00:12:25,978 --> 00:12:28,045
DID YOU WRITE THESE LETTERS     
TO THE UTILITIES COMMISSION?    


191
00:12:28,114 --> 00:12:31,215
AND I'LL WRITE A HUNDRED MORE   
TILL THEY GIVE ME BACK          
MY WORKMAN'S COMP.              


192
00:12:31,284 --> 00:12:34,585
<i>I GOT AN INOPERABLE HERNIA</i>      
<i>WORKING FOR THIS CITY,</i>          


193
00:12:34,654 --> 00:12:37,288
AND THEY THREW ME               
TO THE WOLVES.                  


194
00:12:37,357 --> 00:12:40,057
HOW'D YOU GET THAT LETTER?      
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?               


195
00:12:40,126 --> 00:12:42,226
            I'M CARLSON.        
            THIS IS, UH, NOBEL. 


196
00:12:42,295 --> 00:12:44,695
            HOLD STILL, MAN.    
            I CAN'T SEE         
            YOUR BADGE NUMBER.  


197
00:12:44,764 --> 00:12:48,833
<i>HE DON'T HAVE NO HERNIA.</i>        
<i>HE JUST DON'T WANNA MOVE</i>        
<i>OUT OF THE BASEMENT.</i>            


198
00:12:48,901 --> 00:12:52,737
        SHUT UP, MA! YOU KNOW   
        HOW MY LEGS TINGLE EVERY
        TIME I SIT FOR TOO LONG.


199
00:12:52,806 --> 00:12:54,772
YEAH, AND I KNOW                
WHERE YOU'RE SITTIN'!           


200
00:12:54,841 --> 00:12:58,343
    SIR, WE'RE NOT HERE TO TALK 
    ABOUT YOUR WORKMAN'S COMP.  


201
00:12:58,411 --> 00:13:01,079
        WE WANT TO ASK YOU      
        SOME QUESTIONS          
        ABOUT YOUR WHEREABOUTS. 


202
00:13:01,148 --> 00:13:04,415
HEY, IF YOU THINK               
YOU GOT SOMETHING ON ME,        
YOU COME BACK WITH A WARRANT.   


203
00:13:04,484 --> 00:13:07,451
TILL THEN,                      
ME AND MY MOTHER'S GOT NOTHING  
TO SAY TO YOU MISCREANTS.       


204
00:13:08,454 --> 00:13:11,055
<i>I SHOULD'VE MARRIED</i>             
<i>A DENTIST.</i>                      


205
00:13:11,123 --> 00:13:14,025
AT LEAST THEN                   
HIS TEETH'D BE BETTER.          
                    MA!         


206
00:13:15,661 --> 00:13:17,861
THIS GUY'S CLASSIC              
BOMBER MATERIAL.                


207
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:20,598
FORMER CITY WORKER,             
DOMINEERING MOTHER,             


208
00:13:20,666 --> 00:13:24,768
BASEMENT WORKSHOP,              
A LITTLE ANTISOCIAL BEHAVIOR.   


209
00:13:24,837 --> 00:13:27,038
            <i> I'M NOT CONVINCED.</i> 
        HUH?                    


210
00:13:27,107 --> 00:13:30,208
    HE'S WRITTEN 253 LETTERS    
    TO THE CITY AND COUNTING.   


211
00:13:30,276 --> 00:13:32,543
            IF HE'S CROSSED     
            THE THRESHOLD       
            INTO PLANTING BOMBS,


212
00:13:32,612 --> 00:13:34,745
        DON'T YOU THINK         
        HE WOULD HAVE GIVEN UP  
        THE CORRESPONDENCE?     


213
00:13:34,814 --> 00:13:37,948
DID YOU NOTICE WHAT             
HE CALLED US IN THERE?          
                    MISCREANTS. 


214
00:13:38,017 --> 00:13:42,053
RIGHT. NOBODY USES THAT WORD    
EXCEPT FOR THAT GUY AND--       
                THE FAX BOMBER. 


215
00:13:42,122 --> 00:13:45,323
I'M GONNA GET                   
UNDER THIS GUY'S SKIN           
BEFORE HE HURTS SOMEONE ELSE.   


216
00:14:07,647 --> 00:14:10,081
    <i> [ Electronic Squawking ]</i>   


217
00:14:10,149 --> 00:14:14,251
            WAKE UP! WAKE UP!   
            GOOD MORNING!       


218
00:14:16,423 --> 00:14:18,455
<i>...FIVE, SIX,</i>                   


219
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:21,458
    SEVEN, EIGHT,               


220
00:14:21,528 --> 00:14:23,460
        NINE, TEN--             


221
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,730
        YOU CAN STOP COUNTING.  
        YOU'RE HERE.            
    OH. [ Chuckles ]            


222
00:14:25,798 --> 00:14:29,133
YOU MUST HAVE STEPPED           
INTO THE ROOM.                  
IT'S 11 STEPS TO THE DOOR.      


223
00:14:29,201 --> 00:14:31,803
            I DID.              
            THAT'S VERY GOOD.   


224
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:35,306
IT'S FUNNY, DR. JAROD.          
I USED TO HATE MATH IN SCHOOL.  


225
00:14:35,375 --> 00:14:38,309
NOW MY ENTIRE LIFE              
IS BASIC ARITHMETIC.            


226
00:14:38,378 --> 00:14:40,478
NINE STEPS FROM MY BED          
TO THE BATHROOM,                


227
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:44,082
14 STEPS TO THE HALLWAY,        
SEVEN STEPS TO THE CHAIR.       


228
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:47,451
        JUST BE HAPPY           
        IT'S NOT LONG DIVISION. 


229
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:49,987
        IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY.   
        WHY DON'T WE GO OUTSIDE?


230
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:53,124
OH, NO. I-- I-I THINK           
I'D RATHER STAY HERE.           


231
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,861
                RACHEL,         


232
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,299
        YOU HAVE TO GO OUTSIDE  
        SOMETIME.               


233
00:15:04,804 --> 00:15:09,006
BUT IT WAS SUCH A NICE DAY,     
I DECIDED TO GO                 
ON THE ROOFTOP AT CITY HALL.    


234
00:15:09,075 --> 00:15:11,842
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED            
THE LAST TIME I WENT OUTSIDE.   


235
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:15,579
    YOU WERE IN THE WRONG PLACE 
    AT THE WRONG TIME.          


236
00:15:15,648 --> 00:15:19,183
                BUT THAT IS NOT 
                YOUR FAULT.     


237
00:15:19,251 --> 00:15:21,986
                YOU CAN'T STOP  
                LIVING YOUR LIFE
                BECAUSE OF IT.  


238
00:15:23,322 --> 00:15:26,157
I HEAR HE SET OFF               
ANOTHER BOMB.                   


239
00:15:26,225 --> 00:15:30,194
        YES, HE DID.            
        THANKFULLY,             
        NOBODY ELSE WAS HURT.   


240
00:15:31,698 --> 00:15:34,732
YOU KNOW, WHEN I HAD            
MY EYES BEHIND A CAMERA,        


241
00:15:34,801 --> 00:15:37,068
I COULD SEE THINGS              
NO ONE ELSE COULD SEE.          


242
00:15:37,136 --> 00:15:39,203
<i>I COULD TAKE</i>                    
<i>A THOUSAND SHOTS...</i>             


243
00:15:39,272 --> 00:15:42,006
<i>AND TELL YOU</i>                    
<i>WHICH ONE WAS PERFECT</i>           
<i>BEFORE IT WAS EVEN DEVELOPED.</i>   


244
00:15:43,677 --> 00:15:47,244
I CAN REMEMBER DETAILS          
OF NEARLY EVERY PICTURE         
I EVER TOOK.                    


245
00:15:47,313 --> 00:15:50,114
<i>THAT'S IRONIC.</i>                  


246
00:15:50,183 --> 00:15:53,250
THEY TELL ME                    
HE WAS THERE THAT DAY.          


247
00:15:53,319 --> 00:15:57,555
THAT I MUST HAVE SEEN           
THE MAN WHO DID THIS TO ME      
AS HE WAS SETTING HIS BOMB.     


248
00:15:59,626 --> 00:16:05,396
<i>BUT AS HARD I TRY,</i>              
<i>I CAN'T REMEMBER.</i>               


249
00:16:22,515 --> 00:16:24,249
        I CAN'T BELIEVE         
        THEY THINK ONE OF US... 


250
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:27,651
        IS LEAKING              
        INFORMATION TO JAROD.   


251
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:32,556
[ Sighs ]                       
OH, I WISH I HADN'T EATEN       
THAT POPPY SEED MUFFIN.         


252
00:16:32,625 --> 00:16:35,226
        THEY'RE GIVING US       
        A POLYGRAPH, YOU IDIOT, 


253
00:16:35,295 --> 00:16:37,628
        NOT A URINE TEST.       


254
00:16:37,697 --> 00:16:39,630
I THOUGHT IT WAS BOTH.          


255
00:16:39,699 --> 00:16:42,500
                IT SHOULD BE,   
                FOR YOU.        


256
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:45,236
WHAT-WHAT IS THAT               
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?               


257
00:16:45,304 --> 00:16:48,572
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO HANDLES      
THE INFORMATION AROUND HERE.    


258
00:16:48,642 --> 00:16:51,375
    I'M SORRY.                  
    I'M IN A FILTHY MOOD.       
    LET'S NOT ACCUSE EACH OTHER.


259
00:16:51,444 --> 00:16:55,379
OH, THAT MEANS A LOT            
COMING FROM JAROD'S TEDDY BEAR. 


260
00:16:57,616 --> 00:16:59,583
                MISS PARKER.    


261
00:17:02,656 --> 00:17:04,588
TO CALIBRATE THE MACHINE,       


262
00:17:04,658 --> 00:17:07,291
PLEASE ANSWER THE FOLLOWING     
QUESTION UNTRUTHFULLY.          


263
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:09,760
ARE YOU                         
ELEANOR ROOSEVELT?              
                    YES.        


264
00:17:18,170 --> 00:17:22,707
<i>HAVE YOU PURSUED JAROD</i>          
<i>TO THE BEST OF YOUR ABILITY?</i>    


265
00:17:22,775 --> 00:17:26,110
YES.                            
<i>[ Raines ]</i>                      
<i>BECOME HER, ANGELO.</i>             


266
00:17:26,178 --> 00:17:28,178
<i>TELL ME IF SHE IS LYING.</i>        


267
00:17:28,247 --> 00:17:30,381
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>DID YOU WILLFULLY</i>               
<i>MISFIRE YOUR WEAPON...</i>          


268
00:17:30,449 --> 00:17:33,317
<i>WHEN ATTEMPTING TO APPREHEND</i>    
<i>JAROD IN MIAMI, FLORIDA?</i>        


269
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:36,020
                    WHAT?       
YES OR NO, PLEASE.              


270
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:41,325
                NO.             


271
00:17:41,394 --> 00:17:44,495
SMOKING IS NOT PERMITTED        
DURING A POLYGRAPH.             


272
00:17:57,877 --> 00:17:59,877
HAVE YOU RECEIVED...            


273
00:17:59,946 --> 00:18:02,613
<i>A PERSONAL MESSAGE</i>              
<i>FROM JAROD?</i>                     


274
00:18:05,351 --> 00:18:08,118
        IT WAS A BUNNY.         


275
00:18:09,222 --> 00:18:11,155
            YES.                


276
00:18:16,195 --> 00:18:20,998
<i>DID YOU SECRETLY</i>                
<i>CONTACT JAROD VIA</i>               
<i>A SECURE INTERNET CONNECTION?</i>   


277
00:18:21,066 --> 00:18:23,000
            YES.                


278
00:18:23,069 --> 00:18:26,337
DID YOU ATTEMPT TO PROVIDE HIM  
WITH CLASSIFIED INFORMATION?    


279
00:18:27,807 --> 00:18:31,876
    YES, BUT WITH A VIEW        
    TO BRINGING HIM HOME.       


280
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:36,513
<i>HAVE YOU EVER SECRETLY</i>          
<i>MET WITH JAROD?</i>                 
            MM-MMM.             


281
00:18:36,582 --> 00:18:40,084
            NO.                 


282
00:18:42,288 --> 00:18:45,089
    IS HE LYING?                


283
00:18:47,393 --> 00:18:50,762
    IS HE THE ONE?              


284
00:18:57,737 --> 00:19:00,438
<i>HAVE YOU EVER USED</i>              
<i>A CONTROLLED SUBSTANCE?</i>         


285
00:19:00,506 --> 00:19:02,373
        [ Clears Throat ]       
        NO.                     


286
00:19:05,311 --> 00:19:10,214
<i>WERE YOU IN THE LAB</i>             
<i>WHEN INFORMATION REGARDING</i>      
<i>JAROD'S ORIGINS WAS LEAKED?</i>     


287
00:19:10,283 --> 00:19:13,484
                YES.            


288
00:19:13,553 --> 00:19:16,019
<i>DID YOU LEAK THE INFORMATION</i>    
<i>JAROD RECEIVED...</i>               


289
00:19:16,088 --> 00:19:19,624
<i>VIA SPECIAL COURIER</i>             
<i>IN MIAMI, FLORIDA?</i>              
                NO.             


290
00:19:23,062 --> 00:19:26,563
<i>HAVE YOU EVER LIED</i>              
<i>TO THE CENTRE?</i>                  
                NO.             


291
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:30,600
            [ Gasping ]         


292
00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:40,143
    HE'S THE LEAK,              
    ISN'T HE, ANGELO?           


293
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:39,336
SO, YOU'VE DECIDED TO PUT IN    
A TRANSFER TO FORENSICS, HMM?   


294
00:20:39,405 --> 00:20:41,838
        I'VE JUST BEEN          
        SIFTING THOUGH ALL      
        THE FAX BOMBER DEBRIS.  


295
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:44,975
YOU WENT OVER THREE THOUSAND    
PIECES OF EVIDENCE HERE?        


296
00:20:45,044 --> 00:20:48,111
            THREE THOUSAND      
            AND TWENTY-FIVE.    


297
00:20:48,180 --> 00:20:51,215
    - I'VE SPECIFICALLY BEEN    
      STUDYING THE WIRES.       
    - NO, NO, NO.               


298
00:20:51,283 --> 00:20:54,017
THE FEDS, THEY COVERED EVERY    
CENTIMETER OF THAT COPPER.      


299
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:57,387
            I KNOW.             
            I'VE BEEN STUDYING  
            THE ENCASEMENTS.    


300
00:20:57,456 --> 00:21:00,390
        <i> THERE'S NO PATTERN.</i>    
        <i> THIS GUY IS RANDOM...</i>  


301
00:21:00,459 --> 00:21:03,727
    EXCEPT FOR                  
    THE DETONATOR CONNECTORS.   


302
00:21:03,796 --> 00:21:06,163
            HE'S VERY SENSITIVE 
            ABOUT THEM.         


303
00:21:06,231 --> 00:21:08,365
            HE WANTS TO BE SURE.


304
00:21:08,434 --> 00:21:11,636
        THAT'S WHY THEY ALL     
        HAVE EXACTLY THE SAME   
        PARALLEL CUT PATTERN.   


305
00:21:11,704 --> 00:21:13,704
    COME ON.                    
    EXACTLY THE SAME?           


306
00:21:14,974 --> 00:21:16,907
                EXACTLY.        


307
00:21:21,481 --> 00:21:24,114
            <i> NOTICE THE ANGLE</i>   
            <i> OF THE GROOVES</i>     
            <i> ON THE PARALLELS.</i>  


308
00:21:24,183 --> 00:21:27,484
    <i> GIVES US SOMETHING</i>         
    <i> TO RUN DOWN WITH</i>           
    <i> THE KNIFE MANUFACTURERS.</i>   


309
00:21:27,553 --> 00:21:30,187
            AND THE CUT CONTOURS
            CONFIRM THAT HE'S-- 
RIGHT-HANDED.                   


310
00:21:30,256 --> 00:21:32,256
                    <i> YES, SIR.</i>  


311
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,960
        LOW-TECH.               


312
00:21:36,028 --> 00:21:38,396
                VERY.           
<i>MMM.</i>                            


313
00:21:40,466 --> 00:21:42,599
                HELLO.          
                        HEY.    


314
00:21:42,668 --> 00:21:46,603
    HEY. HOW'S THE SPUD         
    OF A THOUSAND FACES?        


315
00:21:46,672 --> 00:21:49,707
        WELL, I ONLY HAVE       
        THE 13-PIECE SET SO,    


316
00:21:49,776 --> 00:21:51,742
    TECHNICALLY,                
    THIS ONE'S ONLY GOT, UH--   


317
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:55,279
ONE HUNDRED AND SEVENTY-NINE.   
I HAVE A PROJECT FOR YOU.       


318
00:21:55,347 --> 00:21:57,781
        I'M UP TO MY EARS       
        IN MILK CARTONS HERE.   


319
00:21:57,850 --> 00:22:00,885
WELL, THIS ONE'S                
VERY SPECIAL TO ME.             


320
00:22:00,953 --> 00:22:03,587
<i>IT'S MY MOTHER.</i>                 
<i>I WAS WONDERING...</i>              


321
00:22:03,656 --> 00:22:05,722
<i>IF YOU COULD AGE HER</i>            
<i>30 YEARS.</i>                       


322
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:09,026
I WANT TO SEE                   
WHAT SHE WOULD LOOK LIKE.       
<i>[ Pager Beeping ]</i>               


323
00:22:11,464 --> 00:22:13,831
            I'LL MAKE IT        
            WORTH YOUR WHILE.   
    HEY, I'LL SEE WHAT I CAN DO.


324
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:15,433
            THANKS.             
                    ALL RIGHT.  


325
00:22:15,501 --> 00:22:18,268
    [ Siren Wailing ]           


326
00:22:24,644 --> 00:22:27,945
IT'S RIGHT OVER THERE UNDER     
THE BUS. IT'S RIGHT OVER THERE  
UNDER THE BUS.                  


327
00:22:28,014 --> 00:22:30,648
                DID THE THREAT  
                COME IN BY FAX? 
IT WAS MORE OF A PHONE CALL.    


328
00:22:30,717 --> 00:22:34,718
ONE OF MY DRIVERS               
FOUND THE UNCLAIMED SUITCASE    
ON THE 3:15 FROM TRAVERSE CITY. 


329
00:22:34,787 --> 00:22:36,787
    ALL RIGHT.                  
    WE'LL TAKE IT FROM HERE.    
THANKS.                         


330
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:38,789
HEY, CAN YOU GUYS               
KINDA HURRY UP?                 


331
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:41,158
'CAUSE I GOT BUSES BACKING      
UP ON ME HERE, MAN, AND I--     


332
00:22:41,226 --> 00:22:43,594
    TAKE AS MUCH TIME           
    AS YOU NEED THEN.           
    THANKS.                     


333
00:23:13,026 --> 00:23:15,592
<i>YOU OKAY?</i>                       
                YEAH.           


334
00:23:15,661 --> 00:23:17,961
            COME ON.            


335
00:23:27,707 --> 00:23:30,741
        <i> [ Buzzing ]</i>            


336
00:23:33,912 --> 00:23:35,846
<i>[ Horn Honks ]</i>                  


337
00:23:48,127 --> 00:23:50,694
GOT A BACKACHE?                 


338
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:56,400
        [ Switches Off ]        


339
00:23:59,705 --> 00:24:02,206
<i>THEY TOLD ME WE WOULD</i>           
<i>HAVE A LOT OF HOAX CALLS</i>        
<i>IN TRAINING,</i>                    


340
00:24:02,275 --> 00:24:04,675
<i>BUT I NEVER THOUGHT</i>             
<i>IT WOULD FEEL LIKE THIS.</i>        


341
00:24:04,744 --> 00:24:07,978
                LET GO, J.      
THAT'S EASY                     
FOR YOU TO SAY.                 


342
00:24:08,047 --> 00:24:10,914
    - IT WAS PRETTY TENSE       
      BACK THERE.               
    - DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.     


343
00:24:10,983 --> 00:24:13,717
    - THAT'S NICE WORK.         
    - OH. YEAH.                 


344
00:24:13,786 --> 00:24:16,053
            FROM MY ARMY DAYS.  
<i>LET ME GUESS.</i>                   


345
00:24:16,122 --> 00:24:19,723
    - YOU GOT DRUNK ONE NIGHT.  
    - BLITZED. [ Chuckles ]     
      MY WHOLE UNIT.            


346
00:24:19,792 --> 00:24:23,327
<i>AFTER GRENADA,</i>                  
<i>THEY STATIONED US DOWN</i>          
<i>AT FORT BUCHANAN, PUERTO RICO.</i>  


347
00:24:23,395 --> 00:24:26,062
        I DO NOT REMEMBER       
        ONE THING THAT HAPPENED 
        THAT ENTIRE MONTH,      


348
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:28,064
            EXCEPT FOR THIS     
            NEEDLE ARTIST.      


349
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:30,133
            HE WAS A            
            SHRIVELED-UP LITTLE 
            PUERTO RICAN GUY... 


350
00:24:30,202 --> 00:24:32,469
    WHO HAD A HOLE-IN-THE-WALL  
    SHOP IN OLD SAN JUAN.       


351
00:24:32,538 --> 00:24:35,505
    HE INKED EVERY SINGLE GUY   
    IN THE WHOLE PLATOON--      
            <i> THE WHOLE PLATOON.</i> 


352
00:24:35,574 --> 00:24:38,242
        YOU KNOW HOW MANY EAGLES
        THIS GUY HAD TO DO      
        IN ONE NIGHT?           


353
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:40,744
            <i> GIVE US A BREAK,</i>   
            <i> WILL YOU, CARLSON?</i> 


354
00:24:40,812 --> 00:24:44,181
YOU PARTNER WITH THIS GUY       
TOO LONG, YOU KNOW HIS OLD UNIT 
LIKE IT WAS YOUR OWN FAMILY.    


355
00:24:49,955 --> 00:24:51,488
<i>[ Rachel ]</i>                      
<i>WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>             


356
00:24:51,557 --> 00:24:53,624
    I'M GOING TO TURN THIS SPACE
    INTO A DARKROOM.            


357
00:24:53,693 --> 00:24:56,526
        I LIVE IN A DARKROOM.   
GOOD.                           


358
00:24:56,595 --> 00:24:58,528
BECAUSE I NEED YOU...           


359
00:24:58,597 --> 00:25:00,964
TO DEVELOP A ROLL               
OF FILM FOR ME.                 


360
00:25:01,967 --> 00:25:03,967
                OH, THAT SMELLS 
                FAMILIAR.       


361
00:25:04,036 --> 00:25:08,072
- I THOUGHT YOU'D REMEMBER IT.  
- IS THIS SOME KIND             
  OF NEW THERAPY?               


362
00:25:08,140 --> 00:25:10,508
CALL IT A SIMULATION.           


363
00:25:10,576 --> 00:25:13,310
                    SIMULATION? 
MM-HMM.                         


364
00:25:13,379 --> 00:25:15,712
I'M GOING TO CREATE             
AN ENVIRONMENT...               


365
00:25:15,781 --> 00:25:20,684
WITH ALL THE STIMULI            
YOU NEED TO RECREATE AN EVENT,  


366
00:25:20,753 --> 00:25:23,086
    AND FOR YOU                 
    TO BECOME SOMEONE.          


367
00:25:23,155 --> 00:25:25,656
            WHO DO YOU WANT ME  
            TO BECOME?          


368
00:25:31,364 --> 00:25:33,464
YOURSELF.                       
                    OH!         


369
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:35,866
                OH, MY CAMERA.  


370
00:25:35,934 --> 00:25:39,170
        OH, I HAVEN'T           
        TOUCHED THIS SINCE THE--


371
00:25:39,238 --> 00:25:41,738
            WELL, SINCE THE DAY 
            AT CITY HALL.       


372
00:25:41,807 --> 00:25:44,675
<i>NOW I WANT YOU TO DEVELOP</i>       
<i>THAT ROLL OF FILM,</i>              


373
00:25:44,743 --> 00:25:47,878
<i>THE PICTURES</i>                    
<i>YOU TOOK THAT DAY.</i>              


374
00:25:47,946 --> 00:25:50,781
            OH, BUT THERE'S     
            NO FILM IN IT.      
<i>I KNOW.</i>                         


375
00:25:50,850 --> 00:25:54,784
I WANT YOU TO DEVELOP           
THE PICTURES IN YOUR MIND.      


376
00:26:07,199 --> 00:26:10,000
            I'M ON THE ROOFTOP  
            AT CITY HALL.       


377
00:26:10,069 --> 00:26:14,971
<i>NATURAL LIGHT IS AT ITS-</i>        
<i>ITS PERFECT ANGLE.</i>              


378
00:26:17,376 --> 00:26:20,411
            THE BUILDING IS--   
            IS CLOSED.          
            IT'S SUNDAY.        


379
00:26:20,479 --> 00:26:24,915
<i>AND I'M, UH, GETTING</i>            
<i>LAST-MINUTE SHOTS</i>               
<i>FOR MY GALLERY OPENING.</i>         


380
00:26:24,984 --> 00:26:27,150
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>ARE YOU ALONE?</i>                  


381
00:26:27,219 --> 00:26:30,520
        I THINK.                
        I-I DON'T SEE ANYONE.   


382
00:26:32,257 --> 00:26:34,658
            I DON'T--           
             I DON'T SEE ANYONE,


383
00:26:34,727 --> 00:26:37,193
            BUT I FEEL A--      


384
00:26:37,263 --> 00:26:40,230
        <i> A TINGLE</i>               
        <i> ON THE BACK OF MY NECK.</i>


385
00:26:42,301 --> 00:26:46,337
<i>[ Footsteps ]</i>                   
<i>I DON'T SEE ANYONE,</i>             
<i>BUT I HEAR SOMETHING.</i>           


386
00:26:46,405 --> 00:26:51,908
<i>WHAT DO YOU HEAR?</i>               
        <i> FOOTSTEPS,</i>             
        <i> WALKING QUICKLY AWAY.</i>  


387
00:26:51,977 --> 00:26:54,078
BUT, UH, YOU DON'T THINK        
ANYTHING ABOUT IT...            


388
00:26:54,146 --> 00:26:56,180
BECAUSE YOU HAVE                
OTHER PICTURES TO TAKE.         


389
00:27:00,486 --> 00:27:02,819
            IT'S RIGHT          
            BEFORE IT HAPPENS.  


390
00:27:11,063 --> 00:27:13,097
    WE CAN STOP THIS            
    IF YOU WANT.                


391
00:27:13,165 --> 00:27:15,299
                NO.             


392
00:27:15,368 --> 00:27:19,603
        I WALK OVER             
        TO WHERE THE FOOTSTEPS  
        ARE COMING FROM,        


393
00:27:19,672 --> 00:27:22,840
                BUT HE'S GONE.  


394
00:27:22,908 --> 00:27:27,578
RACHEL,                         
DO YOU SEE THE BOMB?            


395
00:27:27,646 --> 00:27:30,046
            IT'S ONLY AN INSTANT
            BEFORE THE FLASH.   


396
00:27:32,818 --> 00:27:36,220
<i>DO YOU SEE HIM?</i>                 
                    <i> NO.</i>        


397
00:27:36,288 --> 00:27:40,324
            <i> BUT...</i>             
            <i> I SMELL SOMETHING.</i> 


398
00:27:40,393 --> 00:27:42,392
                    <i> I SMELL--</i>  
    YOU SMELL HIM.              


399
00:27:44,196 --> 00:27:46,330
            IT MUST BE, UM--    


400
00:27:46,398 --> 00:27:49,399
        I DON'T-- I DON'T KNOW  
        WHAT IT IS.             


401
00:27:49,468 --> 00:27:51,468
                IT-IT'S COLOGNE.


402
00:27:51,536 --> 00:27:55,272
            <i> NO, IT-IT'S, UM,</i>   
            <i> MEDICINE, MENTHOL.</i> 


403
00:27:55,341 --> 00:27:59,877
        - WHAT ATHLETES PUT     
          ON SORE MUSCLES.      
        - LIQUID HEAT.          


404
00:28:04,116 --> 00:28:06,049
        THANK YOU.              


405
00:29:10,783 --> 00:29:13,483
    - ARE YOU STEVEN JOHNSON?   
    - YEAH.                     


406
00:29:13,552 --> 00:29:15,485
            SPECIAL AGENT       
            JAROD WEBSTER.      


407
00:29:15,554 --> 00:29:18,455
    F.B.I.?                     
    WHAT DID I DO?              


408
00:29:18,524 --> 00:29:21,558
        NOTHING, MR. JOHNSON.   
        I'M JUST DOING          
        A SECURITY CHECK...     


409
00:29:21,627 --> 00:29:24,327
            ON ONE OF YOUR      
            OLD ARMY BUDDIES,   
            DANIEL CARLSON.     


410
00:29:24,396 --> 00:29:26,329
            <i> HE PUT YOU DOWN</i>    
            <i> AS A REFERENCE.</i>    


411
00:29:26,399 --> 00:29:28,331
IF YOU WANT TO CLEAR CARLSON,   
YOU'RE TALKING TO THE WRONG GUY.


412
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:31,101
- WHY'S THAT?                   
- CARLSON TALKS A GOOD GAME,    


413
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:33,970
BUT THE REST OF THE SQUAD       
HAD TO CARRY HIM                
EVERY STEP OF THE WAY.          


414
00:29:34,039 --> 00:29:36,306
    WELL, THE WAY HE PUTS IT,   
    YOU WERE A VERY TIGHT UNIT. 


415
00:29:38,277 --> 00:29:41,578
WE'D PROBABLY HAVE SHOT HIM     
OURSELVES IF HE HADN'T CAUGHT   
THE SHRAPNEL IN THE SHOULDER.   


416
00:29:41,647 --> 00:29:44,748
    HE HAS THE COMPANY TATTOO   
    ON HIS FOREARM.             


417
00:29:46,952 --> 00:29:50,086
YOU DON'T SEE ANY               
MORONIC LITTLE BIRDS            
ON ME, DO YOU?                  


418
00:29:50,155 --> 00:29:52,589
<i>HELL, CARLSON COME IN</i>           
<i>ONE DAY ALL DRUNK,</i>              


419
00:29:52,658 --> 00:29:55,825
<i>QUEER LITTLE BIRD ON HIS ARM,</i>   
<i>TALKING ABOUT HOW HE WANTED</i>     
<i>THE REST OF US TO GET 'EM.</i>      


420
00:29:55,894 --> 00:29:58,896
GUY'S A DANGEROUS LITTLE        
WANNABE.                        


421
00:29:58,964 --> 00:30:00,697
    WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH   
    FOR YOUR TIME.              


422
00:30:00,766 --> 00:30:02,932
HEY, WHAT'S THE LITTLE WEASEL   
APPLYING FOR, ANYWAY?           


423
00:30:04,603 --> 00:30:07,504
        - BOMB SQUAD.           
        - GOD HELP US ALL.      


424
00:30:09,674 --> 00:30:12,309
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>               
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>YOU PAGED ME?</i>                   


425
00:30:12,378 --> 00:30:15,345
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>OH, YEAH, DUDE.</i>                 
<i>SORRY SANTA WAS A LITTLE LATE,</i>  


426
00:30:29,794 --> 00:30:32,395
        <i> SHE'S STILL BEAUTIFUL.</i> 


427
00:30:32,463 --> 00:30:35,631
<i>NOW, UM, YOU SAID</i>               
<i>YOU'D MAKE IT WORTH MY WHILE.</i>   


428
00:30:35,700 --> 00:30:38,234
    PATIENCE, MR. POTATO HEAD.  


429
00:30:38,303 --> 00:30:41,137
                    THANK YOU.  
    OKAY.                       


430
00:30:42,473 --> 00:30:47,076
    JAROD, THE FAX BOMBER       
    JUST BLEW HIMSELF UP.       


431
00:30:47,145 --> 00:30:49,745
                WHERE'S CARLSON?
    HE PHONED IT IN.            


432
00:30:52,216 --> 00:30:54,417
<i>[ Sirens Wailing ]</i>              


433
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:18,742
            <i> LET ME THROUGH!</i>    
             <i> LET ME THROUGH!</i>   


434
00:31:18,810 --> 00:31:21,277
    LET HER THROUGH. THIS IS    
    HER HOUSE. THIS IS HER SON. 
    LET HER THROUGH.            


435
00:31:21,346 --> 00:31:23,279
                ARE YOU HURT?   


436
00:31:23,348 --> 00:31:25,715
I WASN'T HOME LAST NIGHT.       


437
00:31:25,783 --> 00:31:27,783
        I HAD A DATE.           


438
00:31:31,556 --> 00:31:36,459
            CURTIS? CURTIS,     
            MAMA'S HERE.        
            MA'S HERE, HONEY.   


439
00:31:36,528 --> 00:31:39,629
I HAD A FEELING ABOUT THIS GUY. 
I CAME OVER HERE TO SEE         
IF I COULD GET HIM TO TALK.     


440
00:31:39,697 --> 00:31:42,632
HE MUST HAVE SEEM ME COMING     
BECAUSE THE WHOLE PLACE WENT UP.


441
00:31:42,701 --> 00:31:46,969
- IT KNOCKED ME ALL THE WAY BACK
  TO THE END OF THE DRIVEWAY.   
- IT WAS A NICE PLAY, CARLSON.  


442
00:31:47,038 --> 00:31:49,505
        GET YOURSELF CLEANED UP.
        YOU LOOK LIKE HELL.     
THANK YOU, SIR.                 


443
00:32:03,455 --> 00:32:05,955
            I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN 
            IT WAS HIM.         


444
00:32:10,595 --> 00:32:12,596
ANOTHER CROISSANT,              
MISS PARKER?                    


445
00:32:14,499 --> 00:32:17,500
        COLD COFFEE'S PLENTY.   


446
00:32:17,569 --> 00:32:21,037
                HE ALWAYS SEEMED
                TO BE...        
                A STEP AHEAD,   


447
00:32:21,106 --> 00:32:24,641
        AND THEN SUDDENLY,      
        WE WERE A STEP BEHIND.  


448
00:32:24,710 --> 00:32:28,311
BROOTS HAS THE CLASSIC          
NONCONFRONTATIONAL              
PERSONALITY.                    


449
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:32,582
<i>I DOUBT HE WOULD PUT</i>            
<i>HIMSELF IN HARM'S WAY.</i>          


450
00:32:37,121 --> 00:32:40,090
<i>[ Car Engine Starts ]</i>           


451
00:32:56,908 --> 00:32:59,608
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>WHERE THE HELL</i>                  
<i>IS HE GOING NOW?</i>                


452
00:32:59,677 --> 00:33:02,512
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR?           


453
00:33:12,857 --> 00:33:15,424
COULD HE HAVE FOUND JAROD?      


454
00:33:15,493 --> 00:33:17,827
                I DON'T KNOW.   


455
00:33:17,896 --> 00:33:21,464
            BUT SOMEBODY        
            JUST PUT THEMSELVES 
            IN HARM'S WAY.      


456
00:33:21,533 --> 00:33:23,966
        <i> IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.</i> 


457
00:33:24,036 --> 00:33:26,235
THE SAME BOMBER, WHO WAS SO     
INTELLIGENT HE DIDN'T LEAVE...  


458
00:33:26,304 --> 00:33:29,705
AS MUCH AS A SPECK OF D.N.A.    
BEHIND, ACCIDENTALLY BLOWS UP   
HIS OWN MOTHER'S HOUSE?         


459
00:33:29,774 --> 00:33:33,309
DON'T START WITH ME, NOBEL.     
AND WHY WOULD HE KEEP ALL OF    
HIS BOMB-MAKING EQUIPMENT...    


460
00:33:33,378 --> 00:33:36,245
        IN A BOX IN THE GARAGE  
        WHEN HE HAD HIS OWN     
        BASEMENT WORKSHOP?      


461
00:33:36,314 --> 00:33:40,316
MAYBE HE WAS FEELING THE HEAT   
AND WAS PLANNING TO MAKE A MOVE.
    I DON'T THINK HE'S OUR MAN. 


462
00:33:40,385 --> 00:33:42,418
WHY?                            
IS HE LEFT-HANDED?              


463
00:33:42,486 --> 00:33:44,787
            AS A MATTER OF FACT,
            HE IS.              


464
00:33:47,392 --> 00:33:50,059
THE ISSUE OF GUILT              
IS UP TO A JURY.                


465
00:33:50,127 --> 00:33:52,628
OUR JOB-- COLLECT EVIDENCE.     


466
00:34:01,339 --> 00:34:03,707
            <i> [ Alarm Chirps ]</i>   


467
00:35:40,238 --> 00:35:43,439
<i>[ Man ] NOW WE HAVE AN EXCLUSIVE</i>
<i>WITH OFFICER DAN CARLSON</i>        
<i>OF THE CITY BOMB SQUAD.</i>         


468
00:35:43,508 --> 00:35:46,642
SO, YOU DEFUSED                 
HIS DEVICES AND                 
BROUGHT HIM TO JUSTICE.         


469
00:35:46,711 --> 00:35:49,712
HOW DOES IT FEEL                
TO BE THE MAN WHO               
UNCOVERED THE FAX BOMBER?       


470
00:35:49,780 --> 00:35:53,049
    I'M JUST GLAD               
    THIS NIGHTMARE FOR THE CITY 
    IS FINALLY COMING TO AN END.


471
00:35:55,052 --> 00:35:57,419
        NOT QUITE.              


472
00:36:04,762 --> 00:36:06,896
HERE.                           
        [ Gun Cocks ]           


473
00:36:14,572 --> 00:36:17,907
            WHAT DO YOU--       
            WHAT IS THIS?       
            WHAT ARE YOU DOING? 


474
00:36:17,976 --> 00:36:20,876
        SWEEPERS? IN MY HOUSE?  


475
00:36:23,648 --> 00:36:26,883
            [ Crying ]          
        THAT'S ALL RIGHT. THAT'S
        OKAY. IT'S ALL RIGHT.   


476
00:36:26,951 --> 00:36:29,185
        HE'S IN THE MIDDLE      
        OF THE CUSTODY BATTLE.  


477
00:36:29,254 --> 00:36:32,422
THE P.I. WAS TRYING TO          
DIG UP SOMETHING ON THE EX      
HE COULD USE IN COURT.          


478
00:36:32,490 --> 00:36:36,225
            THE PLANE TICKET?   
TIME FOR LITTLE SUSIE           
TO FLY HOME TO MOMMY.           


479
00:36:36,294 --> 00:36:38,928
            AT LEAST            
            WE'VE CLEARED HIM.  


480
00:36:38,997 --> 00:36:41,030
CLEARED HIM?                    


481
00:36:41,099 --> 00:36:43,899
HE LIED TO THE CENTRE.          


482
00:36:43,969 --> 00:36:48,171
HE NEVER SAID ANYTHING          
ABOUT BEING MARRIED.            
        HE WANTED HIS PRIVACY.  


483
00:36:48,239 --> 00:36:51,140
        NONE OF THAT JUSTIFIES  
        WHAT WE DID.            
        YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT.      


484
00:36:53,544 --> 00:36:55,778
YOU'RE LATE.                    


485
00:36:55,847 --> 00:36:59,782
    WELL, I SPENT ALL MORNING   
    ON THE PHONE WITH A LAWYER. 
    HE DROPPED MY CASE.         


486
00:36:59,851 --> 00:37:02,217
                HMM.            


487
00:37:02,287 --> 00:37:04,320
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT.         


488
00:37:04,389 --> 00:37:07,657
        MMM.                    
        ARE YOU, MISS PARKER?   


489
00:37:07,725 --> 00:37:11,527
    THANKS TO YOU, MY DAUGHTER  
    HASN'T STOPPED CRYING       
    SINCE LAST NIGHT.           


490
00:37:11,596 --> 00:37:14,563
TOMORROW, I HAVE TO SEND HER    
BACK TO HER MOTHER, WHICH IS    
A PLACE SHE DOESN'T WANT TO GO. 


491
00:37:14,632 --> 00:37:16,832
NONE OF THAT HAS ANYTHING       
TO DO WITH THE CENTRE.          


492
00:37:16,901 --> 00:37:18,901
                I WORK HERE.    


493
00:37:20,505 --> 00:37:23,772
        I SOLD MY SOUL          
        TO BE IN THIS PLACE.    
        I'M NOT SELLING HER.    


494
00:37:23,841 --> 00:37:27,776
        SO DON'T MESS WITH HER. 
        AND DON'T MESS WITH ME. 


495
00:38:17,095 --> 00:38:19,995
    HEY, LAMONT,                
    WHAT ARE YOU DOING TONIGHT? 


496
00:38:54,732 --> 00:38:56,598
                HEY, CARLSON.   
    WHAT?                       


497
00:38:56,668 --> 00:38:58,834
            YOU'D BETTER TAKE   
            A LOOK AT THIS.     


498
00:39:04,642 --> 00:39:06,642
WHAT?                           


499
00:39:07,812 --> 00:39:10,179
UGH. THIS IS                    
SOME KIND OF HOAX.              


500
00:39:10,248 --> 00:39:13,115
    NOW, WE KNOW                
    THE-THE FAX BOMBER          
    IS IN A HOSPITAL BED.       


501
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:15,284
            WELL, I GUESS HE    
            CHECKED HIMSELF OUT.


502
00:39:15,353 --> 00:39:17,519
                    LET'S GO.   


503
00:39:21,359 --> 00:39:24,227
        MAIN ELEVATOR BANKS.    
RIGHT OVER THERE.               


504
00:39:26,364 --> 00:39:29,732
    - COME ON!                  
    - MAYBE WE SHOULD WAIT      
      FOR BACKUP.               


505
00:39:29,801 --> 00:39:31,634
    AND MISS OUR CHANCE         
    TO BE HEROES?               


506
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:33,635
<i>COME ON.</i>                        


507
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:45,314
            WHOA.               
            ANOTHER BAD BETTY.  


508
00:39:45,383 --> 00:39:47,917
                    OH, GOD.    


509
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:51,887
            LET'S NOT RUSH      
            INTO ANYTHING HERE. 


510
00:39:53,257 --> 00:39:56,959
OH, LOOK.                       
HE LEFT A NOTE.                 


511
00:39:58,529 --> 00:40:01,163
                <i> CAREFUL. SLOW.</i> 


512
00:40:06,337 --> 00:40:09,572
"THIS TIME IT'S REAL."          


513
00:40:09,641 --> 00:40:11,840
HMM. SEE?                       


514
00:40:11,909 --> 00:40:13,342
NO!                             
<i>[ Bell Dings ]</i>                  


515
00:40:17,014 --> 00:40:19,415
<i>FORGET IT, CARLSON.</i>             


516
00:40:19,484 --> 00:40:23,285
THIS IS THE EXPRESS.            
IT WON'T STOP FOR 60 FLOORS.    


517
00:40:23,354 --> 00:40:26,589
<i>UH-OH.</i>                          
<i>SIXTY FLOORS IF WE'RE LUCKY.</i>    


518
00:40:26,658 --> 00:40:31,093
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?   
- BAROMETRIC DETONATOR.         


519
00:40:31,162 --> 00:40:34,263
DESIGNED TO DETONATE            
AT ALTITUDES 600 OR 700 FEET.   


520
00:40:34,332 --> 00:40:38,201
<i>MY GUESS IS WE'RE GOOD</i>          
<i>FOR 45, 50 FLOORS, TOPS.</i>        


521
00:40:41,505 --> 00:40:46,174
    - WE GOTTA GET OUT OF HERE! 
    - NO, WE'VE GOTTA           
      DEFUSE THIS BOMB.         


522
00:40:46,243 --> 00:40:49,111
    NO, THERE'S NO TIME!        
<i>OH, THERE'S PLENTY OF TIME.</i>     


523
00:40:49,179 --> 00:40:51,814
<i>IT SHOULD BE EASY FOR YOU.</i>      


524
00:40:51,882 --> 00:40:54,683
        IT'S JUST LIKE          
        ALL THE OTHER BOMBS     
        YOU USED TO MAKE.       


525
00:40:54,752 --> 00:40:56,485
        HUH?                    
<i>YOU KNOW,</i>                       


526
00:40:56,554 --> 00:40:59,822
    THE BOMBS YOU DEFUSED...    


527
00:40:59,891 --> 00:41:04,359
<i>SO YOU COULD BE A HERO</i>          
<i>JUST LIKE YOUR BIG BROTHER WAS?</i> 
        WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?   


528
00:41:04,428 --> 00:41:08,563
JUST YOUR AVERAGE,              
EVERYDAY MISCREANT.             


529
00:41:08,632 --> 00:41:11,833
<i>AND SOMEONE WHO DOESN'T THINK</i>   
<i>THAT RACHEL NEWTON SHOULD HAVE</i>  
<i>LOST HER EYESIGHT...</i>            


530
00:41:11,902 --> 00:41:13,836
SO THAT YOU COULD BE            
PUT IN THE LIMELIGHT.           


531
00:41:13,905 --> 00:41:17,306
        NOW, LISTEN TO ME JAROD.
        I DID NOT EXPECT        
        ANYBODY TO GET HURT.    


532
00:41:17,375 --> 00:41:20,710
TELL THAT TO CURTIS HARING.     
HE WAS THE GUY                  
YOU TRIED TO BLOW UP,           


533
00:41:20,778 --> 00:41:22,311
SO YOU COULD                    
COVER YOUR TRACKS.              


534
00:41:22,379 --> 00:41:24,713
ALL RIGHT! THAT'S ENOUGH!       
NOW, COME ON! DEFUSE THIS THING!


535
00:41:24,782 --> 00:41:27,583
NOT SO COOL UNDER PRESSURE      
WHEN IT'S NOT YOUR OWN BOMB.    


536
00:41:27,651 --> 00:41:32,021
<i>BUT YOU SEE,</i>                    
<i>PEOPLE THAT PLANT BOMBS,</i>        
<i>THEY'RE COWARDS AT HEART.</i>       


537
00:41:32,089 --> 00:41:36,725
AND SINCE I PLANTED THIS ONE,   
I DON'T WANT TO STICK AROUND    
TO WATCH IT BLOW.               


538
00:41:36,794 --> 00:41:39,195
        -<i> [ Bell Dings ]</i>        
        - UH-OH.                


539
00:41:40,264 --> 00:41:44,700
    TWENTIETH FLOOR.            
    BETTER GET TO WORK.         


540
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:52,775
    HOPE YOU CAN FIGURE OUT     
    WHICH WIRE TO SNIP.         


541
00:41:58,015 --> 00:42:00,015
            BYE-BYE, HERO.      


542
00:42:01,318 --> 00:42:03,853
        NO! JAROD!              


543
00:42:03,922 --> 00:42:05,887
        JAROD!                  


544
00:42:05,956 --> 00:42:07,889
            [ Beeping ]         


545
00:42:15,933 --> 00:42:18,267
<i>[ Thudding ]</i>                    


546
00:42:36,787 --> 00:42:39,522
    I GUESS THAT'S WHY          
    THEY CALL IT THE EXPRESS.   


547
00:42:59,844 --> 00:43:02,344
<i>[ Rapid Beeping ]</i>               


548
00:43:02,412 --> 00:43:06,314
<i>[ Electronic Male Voice ]</i>       
<i>TEN, NINE, EIGHT,</i>               


549
00:43:06,383 --> 00:43:09,485
<i>SEVEN, SIX,</i>                     


550
00:43:09,553 --> 00:43:12,421
<i>FIVE, FOUR,</i>                     


551
00:43:12,490 --> 00:43:15,857
<i>THREE, TWO,</i>                     


552
00:43:15,926 --> 00:43:17,793
<i>ONE.</i>                            


553
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:19,795
<i>KABOOM.</i>                         


554
00:43:23,801 --> 00:43:25,801
            YOU'RE UNDER ARREST,
            CARLSON.            


555
00:43:36,447 --> 00:43:38,948
<i>[ Curtis ]</i>                      
<i>...THAT ALL OF YOU</i>              
<i>AT CITY HALL...</i>                 


556
00:43:39,016 --> 00:43:41,817
    WILL PAY EGREGIOUSLY        
    FOR WHAT HAS HAPPENED TO ME.


557
00:43:41,886 --> 00:43:43,886
ARE YOU SURE                    
YOU WANT TO SAY THAT?           
                    SAY WHAT?   


558
00:43:43,954 --> 00:43:46,255
"EGREGIOUSLY"?                  
    WHO'S WRITING THIS LETTER?  


559
00:43:46,324 --> 00:43:48,891
I WAS ONLY MAKING               
A SUGGESTION.                   
                IT'S MY LETTER! 


560
00:43:48,959 --> 00:43:51,727
ALL RIGHT, ALREADY.             
WHAT DO YOU WANT FROM ME?       
                        MA!     


561
00:43:51,795 --> 00:43:53,729
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW             
WHAT IT MEANS.                  
                    DO TOO!     


562
00:43:53,797 --> 00:43:55,564
WELL, I CAN SPELL IT.           
                JUST WRITE IT!  


563
00:43:55,632 --> 00:43:58,701
<i>E, G, R--</i>                       
            <i> GET MY DICTIONARY!</i> 


564
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:02,905
I'M NOT GOING                   
IN THAT SMELLY BASEMENT.        
    OHH! THERE'S A FLY ON ME.   


565
00:44:02,974 --> 00:44:04,706
    "EGREGIOUSLY."              
            A FLY ON ME!        
            AAH!                


566
00:44:35,472 --> 00:44:38,907
<i>[ Knocking ]</i>                    
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>MORNING, MAY.</i>                   


567
00:44:38,976 --> 00:44:41,510
<i>WHERE'S RACHEL?</i>                 
            THERE'S SOMETHING   
            YOU SHOULD SEE.     


568
00:44:47,084 --> 00:44:49,785
    <i> TOOK HER ABOUT A HALF HOUR</i> 
    <i> TO GET DOWN THERE.</i>         


569
00:44:49,853 --> 00:44:52,555
            <i> BUT SHE GOT THERE</i>  
            <i> ALL BY HERSELF.</i>    


570
00:45:09,440 --> 00:45:12,975
        <i> HE'S STILL SEARCHING,</i>  
        <i> MR. PARKER.</i>            


571
00:45:13,043 --> 00:45:14,977
                BUT WE WILL     
                FIND THE LEAK.  


572
00:45:16,314 --> 00:45:18,914
<i>I PROMISE YOU THAT.</i>             


573
00:45:22,386 --> 00:45:25,320
            <i> DID YOU FIND</i>       
            <i> SOMETHING, ANGELO?</i> 


574
00:45:34,031 --> 00:45:36,298
            KEEP WORKING.       


575
00:45:36,367 --> 00:45:38,367
        KEEP WORKING.           


576
00:46:06,263 --> 00:46:08,630
<i>[ Keyboard Clacking ]</i>           


577
00:46:42,700 --> 00:46:43,699
            [ Mews ]            


